    <h2>Understanding Mental Health</h2>
    <p>Mental health is an essential part of our overall well-being, yet there are often misunderstandings and stigmas associated with it. Let's break down the barriers and increase our understanding:</p>
    
    <h3>What is Mental Health?</h3>
    <p>Mental health refers to our emotional, psychological, and social well-being. It affects how we think, feel, and act, influencing how we handle stress, relate to others, and make choices.</p>
    
    <h3>Common Misconceptions:</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Mental health issues are a sign of weakness:</strong> In reality, mental health challenges can affect anyone, regardless of strength or character.</li>
        <li><strong>People with mental health issues are violent:</strong> The majority of individuals with mental health conditions are not violent; they are more likely to be victims of violence.</li>
        <li><strong>Mental health problems are not real illnesses:</strong> Mental health conditions are legitimate medical conditions that require attention and care, just like physical illnesses.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Breaking the Stigma:</h3>
    <p>By educating ourselves and fostering open conversations, we can break the stigma surrounding mental health. Let's encourage empathy, understanding, and support for those facing mental health challenges.</p>
